The paper is about dynamic malware analysis using deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a novel feature extraction approach and a deep neural network architecture, which involves both feature engineering and feature learning. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the design of the architecture, which involves bidirectional LSTM networks, which is a common technique used in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique used in neural networks (cs.NE).
